The xmlBlaster test suite
=========================


   The xmlBlaster test suite is based on the
   JUNIT 1.0 testsuite from Kent Beck and Erich Gamma.

   see http://members.pingnet.ch/gamma/junit.htm



Start the test suite:
---------------------

   Simply type:

      make test



Start the test suite manually:
------------------------------

   Start xmlBlaster server:

      jaco org.xmlBlaster.Main

   Start the test suite with GUI support:

      jaco -Djava.compiler= test.ui.TestRunner testsuite.org.xmlBlaster.TestAll

   For command line output invoke:

      jaco -Djava.compiler= test.textui.TestRunner testsuite.org.xmlBlaster.TestAll

   Start one test without testsuite (and with debugging output on console):

      jaco -Djava.compiler= testsuite.org.xmlBlaster.TestUnSub -trace true -dump true -calls true -time true


   Test RMI:

      jaco -Djava.compiler= -Dclient.protocol=RMI test.ui.TestRunner testsuite.org.xmlBlaster.TestAll

   Test XML-RPC:

      jaco -Djava.compiler= -Dclient.protocol=XML-RPC test.ui.TestRunner testsuite.org.xmlBlaster.TestAll


Note that Junit is extended by some methods in TestCase.java
------------------------------------------------------------

  3 methods assertNotEquals(...) are added
  the modified test.jar is distributed in $XMLBLASTER_HOME/lib/test.jar



This is how junit is build new:
-------------------------------

   export JUNIT_HOME=/opt/junit
   export CLASSPATH=${CLASSPATH}:${JUNIT_HOME}/test.jar:${JUNIT_HOME}

   cd $JUNIT_HOME/test/framework/
      jikes *.java

   cd $JUNIT_HOME
      jar uvf test.jar test/framework/*.class

   Add the test.jar file to the xmlBlaster/lib directory



Building html files with syntax highlighting from java source
_____________________________________________________________

   The xmlBlaster/doc/requirement html files have links
   on the testsuite examples.
   Type 'make html' to generate the html files.
